sentences: Elena Asachi, née Teyber, (30 October 1789 – May 1877) was a Romanian pianist, singer and composer of Austrian birth.
Elena Teyber was born in Vienna and studied music under her father as a child in Dresden.
Later she studied in Vienna under opera singer Domenico Donzelli.
After completing her studies, she became a professor at Iaşi Conservatory where she was known as a pianist and composer from 1827 to 1863.
Se starb, sagst tu (G. Asachi, translated by E. Asachi) 1837
